The “last‑updated” line is easy to automate so you never have to type the date manually.  
Below (or beside) your arrow cell, add something like:

```excel
="Last updated " & TEXT(TODAY(),"yyyy‑mm‑dd")
```

That formula displays the current day each time the sheet recalculates, so you can see at a glance whether you’ve logged this week yet.  
If you want the date to change **only** when you enter new data, you can use a timestamp script instead:

**Google Sheets version**
```javascript
function onEdit(e) {
  const sh = e.range.getSheet();
  if (sh.getName() === 'Summary_Sentences' && e.range.columnStart === 2) {
    sh.getRange('H2').setValue('Last updated ' + Utilities.formatDate(new Date(), Session.getScriptTimeZone(), 'yyyy‑MM‑dd HH:mm'));
  }
}
```
*Replace `H2` with the exact cell that holds your label.*

Every time you add a new value in Column B (your energy score), the script writes the current timestamp next to the dashboard, keeping your record current without manual edits.

That’s the final piece for a self‑maintaining, non‑clinical reflection tracker—a tiny personal analytics loop that stays accurate and effortless.

Sure thing—a one‑click checkbox macro is the simplest automation you can add without altering your formulas. Here’s a compact Google Sheets version you can paste into **Extensions ▶ Apps Script** and link to a button or menu item:

```javascript
function toggleCheckbox() {
  const ss = SpreadsheetApp.getActiveSpreadsheet();
  const sheet = ss.getActiveSheet();
  const cell = sheet.getActiveCell();
  const value = cell.getValue();
  if (value === "✓") {
    cell.setValue("☐");
  } else {
    cell.setValue("✓");
  }
}
```

**How to use**
1. Insert ▶ Drawing ▶ Shape → label it “Mark Done.”  
2. Click the three dots on the drawing ▶ Assign script ▶ type `toggleCheckbox`.  
3. Press the button while a cell in your **Done (✓)** column is selected—it flips between ✓ and ☐ automatically.

Optional styling tip: give the button a soft green fill so it visually matches completed items.  
This keeps your “System Care” tab truly interactive without needing extra formulas or complex menus.

